name: K+-transporting ATPase
classes: Acting on acid anhydrides to catalyse transmembrane movement of substances
reaction: ATP + H2O + K+out = ADP + phosphate + K+in [RN:R00086]
comment: A P-type ATPase that undergoes covalent phosphorylation during the transport cycle. A bacterial enzyme of di(heterotetrameric) structure that is involved in K+ import. The probable stoichiometry is one ion per ATP hydrolysed.

references.title: Characterization of the phosphorylated intermediate of the K+-translocating Kdp-ATPase from Escherichia coli.
Assembly of the Kdp complex, the multi-subunit K+-transport ATPase of Escherichia coli.
